# Keep FEATURES.md and PROJECT_INDEX.md Current

After implementing something new (feature, module, endpoint, component, significant refactor), evaluate whether these files need an update:

## FEATURES.md

Update when:
- A new user-facing feature was added or removed
- An existing feature's behavior changed significantly
- A feature was deprecated or replaced

Skip when:
- The change is purely internal (refactor, bugfix, dependency bump)
- The feature is already documented and unchanged

## PROJECT_INDEX.md

Update when:
- New files, modules, or directories were created
- Files were renamed, moved, or deleted
- New endpoints, routes, or entry points were added
- Architecture or dependencies changed meaningfully
- New environment variables or external integrations were introduced

Skip when:
- Only code within existing files changed (logic fixes, style tweaks)
- The change doesn't affect structure, navigation, or module boundaries

## Workflow

1. Complete the implementation
2. Briefly assess: "Did I add, remove, rename, or restructure anything?"
3. If yes, suggest: "This change affects [X]. Want me to update FEATURES.md / PROJECT_INDEX.md?"
4. Only update after the user confirms
